.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-pomodoro \- A colorful terminal focus timer based on the Pomodoro Technique. Alternates between work and break blocks for a configurable number of cycles, displays a live progress bar during each block, and logs completed sessions to a persistent file.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility pomodoro
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
A colorful terminal focus timer based on the Pomodoro Technique. Alternates between work and break blocks for a configurable number of cycles, displays a live progress bar during each block, and logs completed sessions to a persistent file.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBConfigurable cycles\fP — set custom work duration, break duration, and number of cycles
.IP \(bu 4
\fBLive progress bar\fP — color-coded bar updates every second during work and break blocks
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSession logging\fP — completed work cycles are appended to a persistent log file
.IP \(bu 4
\fBBell and vibration\fP — plays a terminal bell at the end of each block, with Termux vibration support
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSeconds mode\fP — use \fC--unit seconds\fP for quick testing without waiting full minutes
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments launches a guided setup prompt
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _pomodoro/_pomodoro.sh

bash _pomodoro/_pomodoro.sh --work 50 --break 10 --cycles 2

bash _pomodoro/_pomodoro.sh --no-bell

bash _pomodoro/_pomodoro.sh --work 5 --break 2 --cycles 2 --unit seconds --no-bell

bash _pomodoro/_pomodoro.sh
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fC--work N\fP   |   Work block duration (default: \fC25\fP)
\fC--break N\fP   |   Break block duration (default: \fC5\fP)
\fC--cycles N\fP   |   Number of work/break cycles to run (default: \fC4\fP)
\fC--unit minutes\  |  seconds\fP   |   Time unit for durations (default: \fCminutes\fP)
\fC--no-bell\fP   |   Disable terminal bell and Termux vibration
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH PROGRESS BAR
.PP
During each block the timer prints a live updating line:
.PP
.EX
◆ Work focus       23s  ████████████------------
☕ Break time        4s  ██████████████████------
.EE
.PP
Work blocks display in green, break blocks in cyan. The bar fills from left to right as time passes.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH SESSION LOG
.PP
Completed work cycles are logged automatically to:
.PP
.EX
~/.local/state/utilitykit/pomodoro.log
.EE
.PP
Each entry includes a timestamp and the cycle number:
.PP
.EX
2026-06-20 14:32:01 | completed work cycle 1
2026-06-20 14:58:44 | completed work cycle 2
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH POMODORO TECHNIQUE REFERENCE
.PP
Style   |   Work   |   Break   |   Cycles
Classic   |   25 min   |   5 min   |   4
Long focus   |   50 min   |   10 min   |   2
Ultradian   |   90 min   |   20 min   |   2
Quick test   |   5 sec   |   2 sec   |   3
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   All cycles completed successfully
\fC1\fP   |   Unknown option passed
